cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about concept tagging, which is a subtask of natural language understanding (NLU). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also discusses various machine learning algorithms, including generative, discriminative, and deep learning methods, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithms on public datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
